'''战术射击游戏'''是一种包括[[第一人称射击|第一人称射击]]和[[第三人称射击|第三人称射击]]的[[電子遊戲類型|電子游戏類別]]。这些游戏通常模拟真实的战斗。在这种游戏中，比起在其他游戏中重視的快速反应能力，此類遊戲更需要战术和谨慎。涉及军事战斗的战术射击游戏有时被称为“士兵模拟”（''soldier sims''）。<ref name=ssim>{{cite web | last = Richardson | first = Ben | title = Armed Assault | publisher = GamesRadar UK | date = April 20, 2006 | url = http://www.gamesradar.com/pc/arma-armed-assault-import/preview/armed-assault/a-2006042016405064066/g-20060420163514716024 | accessdate = 2009-02-13 | archive-date = 2011-06-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110616035112/http://www.gamesradar.com/pc/arma-armed-assault-import/preview/armed-assault/a-2006042016405064066/g-20060420163514716024 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>IGN Staff [http://uk.pc.ign.com/articles/100/100508p1.html Operation Flashpoint Goes to War] {{Wayback|url=http://uk.pc.ign.com/articles/100/100508p1.html |date=20120206221729 }} ''IGN'' (Dec 14, 2001) Retrieved on Feb 7, 2008</ref><ref>Adams, David [http://uk.pc.ign.com/articles/687/687290p1.html America's Army Linked Up] {{Wayback|url=http://uk.pc.ign.com/articles/687/687290p1.html |date=20120211155834 }} ''IGN'', (Feb 9, 2006) Retrieved on Feb 7, 2008</ref>

== 游戏设计 ==

根据IGN的定义，战术射击“是关于谨慎，小心，合作，协调，规划，以及移动。在这些游戏中，决定性的推进，快速移动以提供掩护，战术撤退，以及获得高分不仅对成功很重要，但是在这样一种方式的平衡使这些成为一种愉快的游戏行为。”<ref>{{cite web |author=Ivan Sulic |url=http://pc.ign.com/articles/358/358691p2.html |title=Tactical Ops – PC Review at IGN |publisher=Pc.ign.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-28 |archive-date=2012-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026021812/http://www.ign.com/articles/2002/05/07/tactical-ops?page=2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

战术射击游戏的设计尊崇真实主义。<ref name="fundamentals"/>玩家被一颗子弹打死是很寻常的，<ref name="hiddenanddangerous"/>因此玩家必须比在其他[[射击游戏|射击游戏]]要更谨慎。<ref name="fundamentals">{{cite book|last=Rollings|first=Andrew|authorlink=|coauthors=Ernest Adams|title=Fundamentals of Game Design|publisher=Prentice Hall|year=2006|location=|url=http://wps.prenhall.com/bp_gamedev_1/54/14053/3597646.cw/index.html|access-date=2014-02-07|archive-date=2017-12-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231072651/http://wps.prenhall.com/bp_gamedev_1/54/14053/3597646.cw/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>寫實的武器[[计算机模拟|建模]]相當被重視，<ref name = "deltaforce">{{cite web | url = http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/deltaforcetaskforcedagger/review.html | publisher = GameSpot | title = Delta Force: Task Force Dagger Review | author = Scott Osborne | date = 2002-07-16 | accessdate = 2009-03-10 | archive-date = 2011-10-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111023044344/http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/deltaforcetaskforcedagger/review.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>以及比起其他游戏功能更為有限的{{link-en|強化物品|Power-up}}。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamepro.com/article/features/3729/tactical-shooters-the-second-generation/ |title=Feature: Tactical Shooters: The Second Generation |author=Jason Samuel |date=2000-11-29 |accessdate=2009-04-22 |publisher=GamePro |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607065033/http://www.gamepro.com/article/features/3729/tactical-shooters-the-second-generation/ |archivedate=2011-06-07 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>这限制了在其他射击游戏中常见的个人英雄主义，因此[[军事战术|战术]]变得越来越重要。<ref>Fudge, James, [http://uk.cube.gamespy.com/gamecube/tom-clancys-rainbow-six-3/505147p1.html Rainbow Six 3 to GameCube (GCN)] {{Wayback|url=http://uk.cube.gamespy.com/gamecube/tom-clancys-rainbow-six-3/505147p1.html |date=20200919055231 }} ''GameSpy'' (April 8, 2004), Retrieved on Feb 7, 2008</ref><ref>Tamte, Peter [http://uk.pc.gamespy.com/pc/close-combat-first-to-fight/563591p1.html Close Combat: First to Fight – Vol #3 (PC)] {{Wayback|url=http://uk.pc.gamespy.com/pc/close-combat-first-to-fight/563591p1.html |date=20200924005156 }} ''GameSpy'' (Nov. 4, 2004) Retrieved on Feb 7, 2008</ref><ref>[http://uk.pc.ign.com/articles/386/386807p1.html Special Forces Pack Released] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120206221716/http://uk.pc.ign.com/articles/386/386807p1.html |date=2012-02-06 }} ''IGN'' (Feb 20, 2003) Retrieved on Feb 7, 2008</ref>

总的来说，战术射击游戏的节奏比其他[[动作游戏|动作游戏]]要慢。<ref name="starwars"/>跳跃的技术有时被降低以提高真实性，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://planetgearsofwar.gamespy.com/View.php?view=Articles.Detail&id=7 |publisher=GameSpy |author=RaptoR |title=Gears of War Review |date=2006-11-25 |accessdate=2009-04-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090212133203/http://planetgearsofwar.gamespy.com/View.php?view=Articles.Detail&id=7 |archivedate=2009-02-12 }}</ref>某些游戏甚至省略跳跃键。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://reviews.cnet.com/xbox-games/tom-clancy-s-ghost/4505-9582_7-31259290.html | publisher = CNET | title = Tom Clancy's Ghost Recon 2 (Xbox) | author = Erik Wolpaw | date = 2004-11-22 | accessdate = 2009-04-18 | archive-date = 2014-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140221215418/http://reviews.cnet.com/xbox-games/tom-clancy-s-ghost/4505-9582_7-31259290.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>相较于强调跑动和射击的游戏，战术射击游戏需要更多的谨慎和耐心（利用掩體以及避免在开阔地区活动），<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.videogamer.com/xbox360/gears_of_war/preview-279.html | title = Gears of War Hands-on Preview | author = Andrew Vandervell | date = 2006-10-16 | publisher = videogamer.com | accessdate = 2009-04-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081204124245/http://www.videogamer.com/xbox360/gears_of_war/preview-279.html | archive-date = 2008-12-04 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>在战术射击游戏中，射击在玩家跑动时变得十分不精确，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.gamespy.com/previews/october02/ghostreconxbox/ |title=Tom Clancy's Ghost Recon (Xbox) |author=Shane Satterfield |date=2002-10-16 |publisher=GameSpy |accessdate=2009-04-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091023174537/http://archive.gamespy.com/previews/october02/ghostreconxbox/ |archivedate=2009-10-23 }}</ref>而匍伏或者蹲姿则有利于提高准度。玩家往往可以使用[[腰射|腰射]]姿势（''"hippie"''），这种姿势虽不精确但能提高视野，或使用瞄准镜放大以提高精度，但这将缩小视野。一些战术射击游戏甚至删除了其他的[[第一人称射击游戏|第一人称射击游戏]]能够看到的{{link-en|十字线|Reticle}}，以实现高度的真实性。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=136261 | title = America's Army: Rise of a Soldier | author = Official Xbox Magazine staff | publisher = CVG | date = 2006-03-25 | accessdate = 2009-04-21 | archive-date = 2014-02-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140228094519/http://www.computerandvideogames.com/136261/reviews/americas-army-rise-of-a-soldier-review/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

许多战术射击游戏使用基于團隊的战斗，在这种情况下玩家需要其他队友的支援。虽然早期的战术射击游戏中电脑控制的玩家只能提供简单的火力支援，[[人工智能|人工智能]]在之后的游戏中进化得能够进行更复杂的小队回应如提供{{link-en|火力压制|Suppressive fire}}。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/deltaforcereloaded/review.html |publisher=GameSpot |title=Delta Force: Xtreme Review |author=Alex Navarro |date=2005-06-07 |accessdate=2009-04-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080515070229/http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/deltaforcereloaded/review.html |archivedate=2008-05-15 }}</ref>在一些有着强大的人工智能的游戏中，玩家可以对其他电脑控制的角色下达命令。<ref name="starwars">{{cite web | url = http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/star-wars-republic-commando/589626p1.html | title = Star Wars: Republic Commando (Xbox) | publisher = GameSpy | author = Will Tuttle | date = 2005-02-21 | accessdate = 2009-03-10 | archive-date = 2005-02-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20050224043117/http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/star-wars-republic-commando/589626p1.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>一些游戏可以在任务之前设定好各角色的行动路线及职务。<ref name="hiddenanddangerous"/>更多游戏则提供了[[多人遊戲|多人在线]]模式，以允许真人玩家制定策略。比其他的射击游戏，战术射击游戏更强调基于团队的策略，因此精确的射击能力以及快速反应能力对于胜利并非那么重要。<ref name="xboxonline">{{cite web|url=http://www.xbox.com/en-US/games/t/tomclancysghostreconadvancedwarfighterxbox360/20060331-ghostingonline.htm |title=Ghosting Online |publisher=xbox.com |author=Alex McLain |accessdate=2009-03-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090409211104/http://www.xbox.com/en-US/games/t/tomclancysghostreconadvancedwarfighterxbox360/20060331-ghostingonline.htm |archivedate=2009-04-09 }}</ref>

关卡的设计通常反映了游戏的设置。例如，玩家可以扮演[[特警|特警]]打击[[恐怖分子|恐怖分子]]和其他犯罪，<ref name="SWAT4"/>或者作为战场上的[[士兵|士兵]]及[[特种部队|特种部队]]的突击兵在真实世界的对抗中遭遇战斗。<ref name="hiddenanddangerous"/>一些游戏发生在完全虚构的宇宙，并包含[[科幻|科幻元素]]。<ref name="starwars"/>每一关将有不同的目标。虽然一些关卡可能只需要玩家打败他们的敌人，<ref name="hiddenanddangerous">{{cite web | url = http://reviews.cnet.com/pc-games/hidden-dangerous-2-pc/4505-9696_7-30989326.html | title = Hidden & Dangerous 2 (PC) | date = 2003-10-28 | publisher = CNET | author = Scott Osborne | accessdate = 2009-03-10 | archive-date = 2014-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140221215415/http://reviews.cnet.com/pc-games/hidden-dangerous-2-pc/4505-9696_7-30989326.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>其他关卡需要护送重要人物（VIP）或者在目标上安装炸弹。<ref name="SWAT4"/>关卡通常设计有检查点（check points）或多重路线（alternate routes）。“强攻”（"run and gun"）经常遇到的重重阻力，取得一些高价值位置的变得尤为重要，或者突袭敌人甚至避开他们的视线完全潜入。<ref name="SWAT4">{{cite web | url = http://pc.ign.com/articles/578/578604p1.html | title = SWAT 4 Impressions | author = Tom McNamara | publisher = IGN | accessdate = 2009-03-10 | date = 2005-01-10 | archive-date = 2011-06-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110613063056/http://pc.ign.com/articles/578/578604p1.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

=== 武器 ===
战术射击游戏往往具有多种模拟实际枪支的[[武器|武器]]，比起普通[[射击游戏|射击游戏]]更加真实，但是过于真實往往会牺牲游戏的[[平衡性|平衡性]]以及[[可玩性|可玩性]]。游戏中的武器及[[彈道學|弹道]]和实际有所差别，这是为了保证多人游戏的平衡性。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gameranx.com/updates/id/5150/article/modern-warfare-3-balanced-guns-a-matter-of-perception-says-infinity-ward/ |title=Modern Warfare 3: Balanced Guns a Matter of Perception, says Infinity Ward |publisher=Gameranx.com |date=2012-02-20 |accessdate=2012-07-28 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127085549/https://gameranx.com/updates/id/5150/article/modern-warfare-3-balanced-guns-a-matter-of-perception-says-infinity-ward/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Ryan Fleming |url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/call-of-duty-modern-warfare-3-review/ |title=Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 3 Review |publisher=Digital Trends |date=2011-11-08 |accessdate=2012-07-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105042020/http://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/call-of-duty-modern-warfare-3-review/ |archivedate=2012-11-05 }}</ref>

比如[[反恐精英|反恐精英]]以及其他游戏允许玩家在躯干中数弹的情况下依然生存（忽略了不同类型的[[防弹衣|防弹衣]]的防弹能力）甚至腿中弹（在现实生活中很少有防弹措施），但在混战中判定一个自动死亡（无论是拳击或刀刺）和“爆头”（包括手枪射击后脑，即使目标戴着头盔）。<ref name="gamespot1">{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.gamespot.com/half-life-counter-strike/reviews/half-life-counter-strike-review-2657769/ |title=Half-Life: Counter-Strike Review |publisher=GameSpot.com |date=2000-11-08 |accessdate=2012-07-28 |archive-date=2012-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121121012143/http://www.gamespot.com/half-life-counter-strike/reviews/half-life-counter-strike-review-2657769/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

比起普通的射击游戏比如[[雷神之锤_(游戏)|雷神之锤]]允许玩家携带整个军火库，战术射击游戏对于玩家的装备有着严格的限制，所以玩家必须根据形势或在团队中的角色仔细选择的武器。[[反恐精英|反恐精英]]的武器系统允许玩家选择一把主武器（[[突击步枪|突击步枪]]，[[机关枪|机关枪]]，[[狙击步枪|狙击步枪]]以及[[霰弹枪|霰弹枪]]）和一把次要武器（[[手枪|手枪]]），这种系统被其它射击游戏所继承，例如[[战地2|战地2]]。

使用或携带重武器如狙击步枪和机枪经常比携带类似冲锋枪和手枪的轻武器移动更加缓慢。玩家发现这种系统有漏洞，例如在[[反恐精英|反恐精英]]中他们通常将武器切换至小刀以加快移动的速度。

[[嚴陣以待|由]]于手榴弹的spam问题，爆炸效果往往被淡化和或只能携带1-2枚手榴弹。

尽管[[双持|双持]]在现实中是不實用以及不准确的，卻经常出现在战术射击游戏中以向電影致敬。而[[沙漠之鹰手槍|沙漠之鹰手槍]]，尽管其重量重，后座力大，以及弹匣容量小使它不适合应用于实际的军事行动中，卻经常在许多战术射击游戏中被设定为一把高杀伤力的武器。例如在[[反恐精英|反恐精英]]以及[[使命召唤4：现代战争|使命召唤：现代战争系列]]當中。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://world.guns.ru/handguns/hg/isr/desert-eagle-e.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2013-11-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022124056/http://world.guns.ru/handguns/hg/isr/desert-eagle-e.html |archivedate=2013-10-22 }}</ref>

